{"title_page": "Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl of Donegall", "text_new": "[[File:All Saints church - stained glass roundel - geograph.org.uk - 1546089.jpg|thumb|Stained glass, All Saints Church, Horsford, Norfolk, showing arms of Dacre Barrett, son of Richard Barrett and Anne Loftus. He married, firstly, Lady Jane Chichester, daughter of Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl of Donegall and Jane Itchingham.<ref>http://www.thepeerage.com/p2999.htm#i29986</ref> Arms of Lennard, Lord Dacre (''Or, on a fess gules three fleurs-de-lys of the first'') quartering Barrett, Lord Newburgh (''Party per pale barry of four counterchanged argent and gules'') impaling the arms of Chichester, Marquess of Donegall quartered with Echyngham (''Azure, fretty argent'').<ref>An Essay Towards a Topographical History of the County of Norfolk: Launditch ...\nBy Francis Blomefield, p.435[https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=wdsvAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA435&lpg=PA435&dq=or+on+a+fess+gules+three+fleurs+or+horsford&source=bl&ots=_5o-P3bEza&sig=D14jXPymJHwS58wWfJzyMvrZbpg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiF5oasxqzeAhUDa8AKHYyRAYQQ6AEwDHoECAQQAQ#v=onepage&q=or%20on%20a%20fess%20gules%20three%20fleurs%20or%20horsford&f=false]</ref>]]\n'''Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl of Donegall''' (died 26 October 1678) was an [[Anglo-Irish]] politician.\n\nChichester was the son of [[Lieutenant Colonel (United Kingdom)|Lieutenant Colonel]] John Chichester (died 1647), of [[Dungannon]], [[County Tyrone]], the latter being the younger brother of [[Arthur Chichester, 1st Earl of Donegall]], and younger son of [[Edward Chichester, 1st Viscount Chichester]].  His mother was  Mary Jones (died 1673),  daughter of [[ Roger Jones, 1st Viscount Ranelagh]]. After his father's death she remarried Colonel  Christopher Copley of [[Wadworth]].  He was [[knight]]ed at [[Whitehall]] in 1660, and served in the [[Irish House of Commons]] as [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Dungannon (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Dungannon]] (1661\u20131666). He was also made an Irish [[Privy Council of Ireland|Privy Counsellor]] in 1672.\n\nChichester married Jane Ichyngham, daughter of Osbern Ichyngham (the younger, died 1655) of [[Dunbrody Abbey|Dunbrody]], County Wexford, a descendant of Sir [[Edward Echyngham]] (died 1527) of [[Barsham, Suffolk]].<ref>'Inquisition, Wexford, James I, no. 55: 1624', in ''Inquisitionum in Officio Rotulorum Cancellariae Hiberniae Asservatarum, Repertorium'', (Commissioners, 1826), I, [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=QLlEju34U1UC&pg=RA4-PA29#v=onepage&q&f=false Part 4 pp. 29-30] (Google).</ref><ref>J. Morrin, 'Historical notes of the Abbey of Dunbrodin', ''Transactions of the Ossory Archaeological Society'', I: 1874-1879 (1879), pp. 407-31, [https://archive.org/details/transactionsofos14osso/page/408/mode/2up at pp. 409-13] (Internet Archive).</ref>\n\nIn 1675 Chichester succeeded his uncle as second [[Earl of Donegall]], inheriting the title under the special remainder granted with it to the male heirs of his grandfather, [[Edward Chichester, 1st Viscount Chichester]]. He was [[Custos Rotulorum]] for [[County Antrim]] and [[Governor]] of [[Carrickfergus]] for twelve years before dying in [[Ireland]] in 1678.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-reg|ie}}\n{{Succession box | before = [[Arthur Chichester, 1st Earl of Donegall|Arthur Chichester]] | title = [[Marquess of Donegall|Earl of Donegall]] | after = [[Arthur Chichester, 3rd Earl of Donegall|Arthur Chichester]] | years = 1675\u20131678 }}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Donegall, Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl Of }}\n[[Category:1678 deaths|Donegall, Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl of]]\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of Ireland|Donegall, Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl of]]\n[[Category:Chichester family|Arthur]]\n[[Category:Year of birth unknown]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Ireland (pre-1801) for County Tyrone constituencies]]\n[[Category:Irish MPs 1661\u20131666]]\n[[Category:Earls of Donegall]]\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\n[[File:All Saints church - stained glass roundel - geograph.org.uk - 1546089.jpg|thumb|Stained glass, All Saints Church, Horsford, Norfolk, showing arms of Dacre Barrett, son of Richard Barrett and Anne Loftus. He married, firstly, Lady Jane Chichester, daughter of Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl of Donegall and Jane Itchingham.<ref>http://www.thepeerage.com/p2999.htm#i29986</ref> Arms of Lennard, Lord Dacre (''Or, on a fess gules three fleurs-de-lys of the first'') quartering Barrett, Lord Newburgh (''Party per pale barry of four counterchanged argent and gules'') impaling the arms of Chichester, Marquess of Donegall quartered with Echyngham (''Azure, fretty argent'').<ref>An Essay Towards a Topographical History of the County of Norfolk: Launditch ...\nBy Francis Blomefield, p.435[https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=wdsvAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA435&lpg=PA435&dq=or+on+a+fess+gules+three+fleurs+or+horsford&source=bl&ots=_5o-P3bEza&sig=D14jXPymJHwS58wWfJzyMvrZbpg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiF5oasxqzeAhUDa8AKHYyRAYQQ6AEwDHoECAQQAQ#v=onepage&q=or%20on%20a%20fess%20gules%20three%20fleurs%20or%20horsford&f=false]</ref>]]\n'''Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl of Donegall''' (died 26 October 1678) was an [[Anglo-Irish]] politician.\n\nChichester was the son of [[Lieutenant Colonel (United Kingdom)|Lieutenant Colonel]] John Chichester (died 1647), of [[Dungannon]], [[County Tyrone]], the latter being the younger brother of [[Arthur Chichester, 1st Earl of Donegall]], and younger son of [[Edward Chichester, 1st Viscount Chichester]].  His mother was  Mary Jones (died 1673),  daughter of [[ Roger Jones, 1st Viscount Ranelagh]]. After his father's death she remarried Colonel  Christopher Copley of [[Wadworth]].  He was [[knight]]ed at [[Whitehall]] in 1660, and served in the [[Irish House of Commons]] as [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Dungannon (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Dungannon]] (1661\u20131666). He was also made an Irish [[Privy Council of Ireland|Privy Counsellor]] in 1672.\n\nChichester married Jane Ichyngham, daughter of Osbern Ichyngham (the younger, died 1655) of [[Dunbrody Abbey|Dunbrody]], County Wexford, a descendant of Sir [[Edward Echyngham]] (died 1527) of [[Barsham, Suffolk]].<ref>'Inquisition, Wexford, James I, no. 55: 1624', in ''Inquisitionum in Officio Rotulorum Cancellariae Hiberniae Asservatarum, Repertorium'', (Commissioners, 1826), I, [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=QLlEju34U1UC&pg=RA4-PA29#v=onepage&q&f=false Part 4 pp. 29-30] (Google).</ref><ref>J. Morrin, 'Historical notes of the Abbey of Dunbrodin', ''Transactions of the Ossory Archaeological Society'', I: 1874-1879 (1879), pp. 407-31, [https://archive.org/details/transactionsofos14osso/page/408/mode/2up at pp. 409-13] (Internet Archive).</ref>\n\nIn 1675 Chichester succeeded his uncle as second [[Earl of Donegall]], inheriting the title under the special remainder granted with it to the male heirs of his grandfather, [[Edward Chichester, 1st Viscount Chichester]]. He was [[Custos Rotulorum]] for [[County Antrim]] and [[Governor]] of [[Carrickfergus]] for twelve years before dying in [[Ireland]] in 1678.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-reg|ie}}\n{{Succession box | before = [[Arthur Chichester, 1st Earl of Donegall|Arthur Chichester]] | title = [[Marquess of Donegall|Earl of Donegall]] | after = [[Arthur Chichester, 3rd Earl of Donegall|Arthur Chichester]] | years = 1675\u20131678 }}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Donegall, Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl Of }}\n[[Category:1678 deaths|Donegall, Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl of]]\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of Ireland|Donegall, Arthur Chichester, 2nd Earl of]]\n[[Category:Chichester family|Arthur]]\n[[Category:Year of birth unknown]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Ireland (pre-1801) for County Tyrone constituencies]]\n[[Category:Irish MPs 1661\u20131666]]\n[[Category:Earls of Donegall]]\n", "