bers        = \n}}\n\n'''Bernays Propaganda''' are a Macedonian [[punk rock]] band.<ref name=\"foster\">{{Cite web|last=Foster|first=Richard|title=Bernays Propaganda interviewed|url=https://louderthanwar.com/bernays-propaganda-interviewed/|work=[[Louder Than War (website)|Louder Than War]]|date=March 11, 2016|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref> They took their name from [[Edward Bernays]]' book ''[[Propaganda (book)|Propaganda]]''.<ref name=\"foster\"/><ref name=\"cole\">{{Cite web|last=Cole|first=Kevin|title=Song of the Day: Bernays Propaganda - Armija|url=https://kexp.org/read/2017/3/21/song-of-the-day-bernays-propaganda-armija/|work=[[KEXP-FM]]|date=March 21, 2017|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref> While their lyrical content contains socio-political lyrics<ref name=\"cole\"/>, their sound has drawn comparisons to [[New Order]]<ref name=\"morris\"/> and [[Tom Tom Club]].<ref name=\"foster2\"/> \n\nTheir 2019 release, ''Vtora mladost, treta svetska vojna'' (''2nd Youth, 3rd World War''<ref name=\"foster2\"/>), features American punk bassist [[Mike Watt]] and Macedonian jazz guitarist [[Toni Kitanovski]] on the track \"Nisto nema da ne' razdeli\".<ref name=\"foster2\"/> The track was also donated to ''Songs From Under the Floorboard, Vol. 1'', proceeds of which go to [[Planned Parenthood]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Sacher|first=Andrew|title=Mike Watt guests on Bernays Propaganda song for Planned Parenthood comp|url=http://www.brooklynvegan.com/mike-watt-guests-on-bernays-propaganda-song-for-planned-parenthood-comp/|work=[[Brooklyn Vegan]]|date=February 19, 2018|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n*''Happiness Machines'' (2009)<ref>{{Cite web|title=Happiness Machines|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/happiness-machines-mw0000819846|work=[[Allmusic]]|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n*''My Personal Holiday'' (2010)<ref name=\"foster2\"/>\n*''Zabraneta planeta'' (2013)\n*''Politika'' (2016)<ref name=\"louder\"/>\n*''Vtora mladost, treta svetska vojna'' (2019)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://bernayspropaganda.bandcamp.com Bernays Propaganda] on [[Bandcamp]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bernays Propaganda}}\n[[Category:Macedonian musicians]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Skopje]]\n[[Category:Macedonian rock music groups]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                = Bernays Propaganda\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| image_size          = \n| background          = group_or_band\n| alias               = \n| origin              = [[Skopje]], [[Macedonia]]<ref>{{Cite book|last=Peddie|first=Ian|title=Popular Music and Human Rights|publisher=[[Routledge]]|year=2016|page=98|ISBN=9781317078197}}</ref>\n| genre               = [[Punk rock]],<ref name=\"foster\"/> [[New wave music|new wave]],<ref name=\"morris\">{{Cite web|last=Morris|first=Kurt|title=Bernays Propaganda: Politika: CD|url=https://razorcake.org/bernays-propaganda-politika-cd/|work=[[Razorcake]]|date=August 25, 2016|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref> [[dance-punk]]<ref>{{Cite web|last=Sacher|first=Andrew|title=High Dive on tour w/ Bernays Propaganda & Nana Grizol, playing Death by Audio w/ Mikey Erg tonight (dates, streams)|url=http://www.brooklynvegan.com/high-dive-on-to/|work=[[Brooklyn Vegan]]|date=May 19, 2014|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n| years_active        = \n| label               = [[Moonlee Records]],<ref name=\"louder\">{{Cite web|last=Comingore |first=Aly|title=New Bernays Propaganda video Premiere|url=https://louderthanwar.com/new-bernays-propaganda-video-premiere/|work=[[Louder Than War (website)|Louder Than War]]|date=September 28, 2016|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref> [[Balkan Veliki]]<ref name=\"foster2\">{{Cite web|last=Foster|first=Richard|title=Bernays Propaganda \u2013 2nd Youth, 3rd World War \u2013 LP review|url=https://louderthanwar.com/bernays-propaganda-2nd-youth-3rd-world-war-lp-review/|work=[[L